<h1 class="hero-h">What Is Claude Sonnet? <em style="color:#00C853;font-style:italic;">Anthropic's daily-driver model.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">Claude Sonnet is the model most B2B teams interact with through Claude Team, Claude Code, and the Anthropic API. Here's what it is, where it fits in the Claude family, and what it's good at.</p>
<div class="tldr"><div class="tldr-l">Short answer</div><p class="tldr-p">Claude Sonnet is the mid-tier model in Anthropic's Claude family — Anthropic's daily-driver model balancing capability and cost. As of mid-2026 the current version is Sonnet 4.7, available through Claude Team, Claude Code, and the API. It's the model behind most B2B Claude workflows because it handles 95%+ of business tasks excellently.</p></div>
</div></div>

<div style="background:#0A1A0A;border-top:1px solid #1A3A1A;border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;padding:1.25rem 2.5rem;">
<div style="max-width:880px;margin:0 auto;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap;font-size:0.78rem;color:#8FAF8F;">
<div>By <a href="/about" style="color:#F0FFF0;text-decoration:none;font-weight:500;">Bill Colbert</a> · <span style="color:#4A6A4A;">Founder, Treetop Growth Strategy</span></div>
<div style="color:#4A6A4A;">Published May 2026 · <a href="/content-library" style="color:#8FAF8F;text-decoration:none;">More from the library</a></div>
</div>
</div>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Where Sonnet fits in the Claude family</h2><p class="body">Anthropic's Claude family has three tiers, roughly: Haiku (smallest, fastest, cheapest), Sonnet (mid-tier workhorse), and Opus (largest, most capable, slowest, most expensive).</p><p class="body">Sonnet is the default for almost every business use case. Strong reasoning, strong writing, strong coding, broad knowledge — at a price point that scales for production usage.</p></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">What Sonnet is good at</h2><ul class="ul"><li>Long-form writing in your voice (with examples loaded).</li><li>Document synthesis — summarize a 100-page PDF and answer nuanced questions.</li><li>Code generation, review, and refactoring across large codebases (especially through Claude Code).</li><li>Structured data extraction (JSON, tables) from messy text.</li><li>Multi-turn conversations holding nuanced context.</li><li>Reasoning under ambiguity — Sonnet asks clarifying questions instead of guessing.</li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">When to step up to Opus</h2><p class="body">Most teams never need Opus. Cases where Opus is worth the cost:</p><ul class="ul"><li>Very long, complex documents requiring genuinely hard reasoning.</li><li>Multi-step research where errors compound.</li><li>Coding tasks where the cost of a mistake is high.</li><li>Generative work where the quality ceiling matters more than throughput.</li></ul><p class="body">For everyday business writing, drafting, synthesis: Sonnet.</p></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">How to access Sonnet</h2><ul class="ul"><li><strong>Claude Team / Enterprise:</strong> Sonnet is the default model for paid business tiers.</li><li><strong>Claude Code:</strong> Sonnet runs in the terminal coding agent.</li><li><strong>Claude API:</strong> Sonnet is available via API for developers building applications.</li><li><strong>Claude.ai Pro:</strong> Sonnet is the default for individual Pro users.</li></ul></div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">FAQ</h2>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Is Claude Sonnet better than GPT-4?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Sonnet and GPT-5-class models trade leadership across benchmarks. For most business workflows, the practical difference is small; for writing-heavy work, Sonnet usually feels slightly more nuanced.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Is Claude Sonnet better than Claude Opus?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Opus is more capable on hard reasoning; Sonnet is faster and cheaper. For most business uses Sonnet is the right choice.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">What does Sonnet cost via API?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Pricing varies by version; check Anthropic's current pricing. Roughly a small fraction of a cent per typical business prompt.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">How often does Sonnet get updated?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Anthropic ships new versions every few months. Each version is generally a meaningful improvement.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Can I switch between Sonnet and Opus mid-conversation?</h3><p class="faq-qa">In the API and Claude Code, yes. In Claude.ai and Claude Team UIs, model selection is per-conversation.</p></div>
</div></section>

